news.title: Hyderabad civic body team kicks off drive to raze 200 buildings in Bandlaguda
news.para: Town planning officials said that the buildings were constructed without layout approval on the 44-acre stretch. The demolition will continue for at least another two weeks, officials said.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal commercial establishments run from DLF colonies, realtor seeks checks
news.para: The developer has shared a list of 742 illegal commercial establishments in its licensed colonies — DLF 1 to 4 — with the department of town and country planning (DTCP) seeking action against owners of these properties.

news.title: Government calls meeting of stakeholders over real estate pendency cases
news.para: According to the consumer affairs ministry, 53,518 consumer cases are pending before the consumer commissions across the country and 9,767 of these are before the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission.

news.title: Housing ministry sets up panel to find way forward for stalled realty projects
news.para: ​The ministry notified the committee almost a year after the Central Advisory Council (CAC) headed by Union housing and affairs minister Hardeep Singh Puri had decided on the move.

news.title: Kandoi Fabrics, directors buy four apartments in South Mumbai's Malabar Hill for Rs 217 crore
news.para: These apartments are spread over a total 18,572 sq ft across the 6th, 7th, 8th, and 9th floor of the super-luxury residential tower Lodha Malabar on Walkeshwar Road.

news.title: Chinese cash trickling back to Asia's property markets
news.para: Chinese demand is helping boost Singapore property prices, Chinese students are snapping up apartments in Sydney and Melbourne, and agents say Chinese interest is ticking up in Thailand.

news.title: ED attaches two Goa plots of HDIL promoters in Patra 'chawl' case
news.para: ​The money laundering case stems from an FIR registered by the Mumbai Police's Economic Offences Wing (EOW) against Guru Ashish Construction Pvt Ltd. and others. The Wadhawans were the directors of this company.

news.title: China Evergrande enters support agreements for debt restructuring
news.para: With more than $300 billion in total liabilities including offshore debt, Evergrande has been at the centre of a property debt crisis in which multiple Chinese developers defaulted over the past year.

news.title: Blackstone REIT limits investor redemptions again in March
news.para: Blackstone has been exercising its right to block investor withdrawals from BREIT since November after requests exceeded a preset 5% of the net asset value of the fund.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA got 48,500 complaints in five years, 60% from Noida
news.para: Of the total complaints registered during the period, UPRERA has been able to dispose of 42,980 (or 88.61 per cent) of them, the real estate regulator said in a statement.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to dole out housing plots for 48,000 poor people in Amaravati
news.para: ​Spread across six villages and 1,135 acres, these plots will be doled out to those who do not own houses in Mandadam, Inavolu, Krishnayapalem, Navuluru, Kuragallu and Nidamanuru, an official release.

news.title: Panchkula court fines HSVP for selling 'disputed' plot
news.para: Aruna Manchanda, 51, a resident of Sector-44, Noida, filed a complaint before the forum alleging that she was allotted a residential plot in Sector-57, Gurugram, on April 20, 2009 for Rs 19.40 lakh by the Estate Officer, HSVP, Sector-34, Gurugram.

news.title: No takers for Pune civic body's gunthewari scheme
news.para: The gunthewari regularization scheme failed to attract many property owners in the last financial year, which ended on Friday, due to its high charges.

news.title: Majority of shopping, commercial complexes in Prayagraj sans safety audit
news.para: Hemant Sharma, assistant director, electrical safety directorate (Prayagraj zone) told TOI, “Majority of commercial establishments in the city have not obtained NOC ( No Objection Certificate) from the Electrical safety directorate till now.

news.title: Pune: June 30 last date to avail property tax concessions
news.para: Tax defaulters will also get another month to clear their dues. They have till April 30 to pay the tax for the 2022-2023 financial year.
